from aap alberto adolfo pinka subject re israel an apartheid state in article adam adam l schwartz write in article aap alberto adolfo pinka write if i decide to go back to the land from which my relative have be expel year ago but first i convert to any other religion can i apply to the law of return a a member of the jewish nation or should i apply a someone whose mother be jewish i not sure about thi but i hope the answer be that you ca apply under the law of return by conversion you elect not to be a part of the jewish nation which wa my point by convert to another religion i do not loose my cultural identity i just loose my religiou identification i consider that define the belong to a nation that claim the right to have a state base on religiou belief be a form of racism what ha change in me between the day before and the day after i convert to loose my be part of the jewish nation at the moment you convert you officially anounced to the world that you do not consider yourself to be part of the jewish nation so why should the jewish nation consider you to be a member to be a part or not of the jeish nation be define by my culture and not by my religion actually if i be an atheist which be in fact like convert into a non-jewish in term of religion i be still consider a part of the jewish nation i can be proud of my jewish culture while not give any importance to the jewish religion or even more i can be proud of my jewish culture while still be convince that the real god be another one i do not know anyone who lose hi memebership to the american nation because he change of god suppose my father be arab suppose he wa bear in palestine in some place which now be part of israel suppose that hi father and hi grandfather a well a or generation before him be bear in that place now suppose there be a war of independence and my father scar by all the fight go on try to take hi family to a place more secure among person he know who speak a language he understand who worship the same god now suppose that that place be some other arab country and now suppose that the war be over and that there be a new country create where my father use to live and that that country be call israel and that in that country jew from all over the world be receive and that person whose family leave thet country generation ago be recieved and grant full-citizenship should i if i decide to go back to my father land where he wa bear a or generation of my family be bear have the right to go back and ask to be recognize in the same way those who be return after year no a a result of war bring by the arab against the jew in an attempt to annihilate israel the arab have lose their claim to land there attacking israel illegal and they now have to pay the price do i feel sorry for the palestinian ye i do but i blame the arab nation for their problem not israel i still believe that we should never confusse the action of state with the individual who happen to live there in the same way that i do not think it be right to blame all israeli for the human right violation of israel i do not think that we should assume that all arab be guilty of the action of the arab state some person flee their home because they be scar now they be in there still suffer for what they be not responsible and remember that we also be tell the same at some point we end in the diaspora and of course i be not for do to other what i do not want do to me adam schwartz adam alberto a pinka aap 